|<------------------------------->[ BEGIN-CRFCF ]<------------------------------->|

NOTICE: UNAUTHORIZED MODIFICATION OF THIS DOCUMENT IS EXPRESSLY PROHIBITED.
EDITING PRIVILEGES ARE EXCLUSIVELY RESERVED FOR THE AUTHOR, DESIGNATED
CONTRIBUTORS, AND AUTHORIZED ARTIFICIAL INTELLIGENCE AGENTS. DOCUMENT INTEGRITY
IS SECURED BY A CRYPTOGRAPHIC CHECKSUM; AUTOMATED VERIFICATION SCRIPTS ARE
EMPLOYED TO DETECT AND PREVENT UNAUTHORIZED ALTERATIONS.

0.  METADATA:

    - RFC:      CONCISE-RFC-000000
    - GROUP:    VS-SCRIPTS
    - TITLE:    CONCISE RFC FORMAT
    - ACRONYM:  CRFCF
    - AUTHOR:   Richeve Bebedor <richeve.bebedor+vs-scripts@gmail.com>
    - CATEGORY: SPECIFICATION
    - STATUS:   DRAFT
    - VERSION:  000000 (0.0.0)
    - CREATED:  2025-12-20
    - CHECKSUM: <SHA-256>

1.  Summary:

    This document defines the canonical structure, sections, and rules for all
    CONCISE-RFC-000000 documents in this repository. It serves as
    the authoritative template for contributors, AI agents, and tooling.

2.  Permission:

    NOTICE: PERMISSION TO USE, MODIFY, COPY, AND/OR DISTRIBUTE THIS DOCUMENT
    AND/OR REPOSITORY IS GRANTED UNDER THE TERMS OF THE LICENSE AGREEMENT
    SPECIFIED IN THE LICENSE FILE. PLEASE REFER TO THE LICENSE FILE FOR DETAILS.

3.  Contents:

    0.  METADATA ........................................................... 009
    1.  Summary ............................................................ 022
    2.  Permission ......................................................... 028
    3.  Contents ........................................................... 034
    4.  Document Status .................................................... 046
    5.  Normative Language ................................................. 057
    6.  Naming Conventions ................................................. 069
    7.  Structure .......................................................... 074
    8.  Compliance ......................................................... 317

4.  Document Status:

    - This document is a DRAFT repository-level RFC.
    - It is not an Internet Standards Track specification.
    - It is intended to enforce,
        - uniformity,
        - clarity,
        - conciseness,
        - and machine-parsable
      structure across all CONCISE-RFC-000000 documents.

5.  Normative Language:

    - The key words,
        - MUST,
        - MUST NOT,
        - SHOULD,
        - and SHOULD NOT
      in this document SHOULD follow RFC-2119 and RFC-8174.
    - This document MUST NOT use MAY.
    - The key word STRICTLY defines absolute and non-negotiable intent and
      SHOULD be interpreted as is.

6.  Naming Conventions:

    - All CONCISE-RFC-000000 document file names MUST be in ALL CAPS.
    - All CONCISE-RFC-000000 document file names SHOULD be one word.

7.  Structure:

    - All CONCISE-RFC-000000 documents MUST be in text format.

    - All CONCISE-RFC-000000 documents MUST NOT exceed 997 lines of text.

    - All CONCISE-RFC-000000 documents MUST be STRICTLY within 83 characters
      in column width.

    - All CONCISE-RFC-000000 documents MUST STRICTLY start with,
        - 1 (|) pipe character, then
        - 1 less than (<) character, then
        - 31 hyphen (-) characters, then
        - 1 opening square bracket ([) character
        - followed by space separated BEGIN-CRFCF, then
        - 1 closing square bracket (]) character
        - 31 hyphen (-) characters, then
        - 1 greater than (>) character, and then, lastly,
        - 1 (|) pipe character.

    - All CONCISE-RFC-000000 documents MUST STRICTLY end with,
        - 1 (|) pipe character, then
        - 1 less than (<) character, then
        - 31 hyphen (-) characters, then
        - 1 opening square bracket ([) character
        - followed by space separated ENDED-CRFCF, then
        - 1 closing square bracket (]) character
        - 31 hyphen (-) characters, then
        - 1 greater than (>) character, and then, lastly,
        - 1 (|) pipe character.

    - All CONCISE-RFC-000000 documents MUST STRICTLY have the NOTICE
      for unauthorized modifications with the following format:

        NOTICE: UNAUTHORIZED MODIFICATION OF THIS DOCUMENT IS EXPRESSLY PROHIBITED.
        EDITING PRIVILEGES ARE EXCLUSIVELY RESERVED FOR THE AUTHOR,
        DESIGNATED CONTRIBUTORS, AND AUTHORIZED ARTIFICIAL INTELLIGENCE
        AGENTS. DOCUMENT INTEGRITY IS SECURED BY A CRYPTOGRAPHIC CHECKSUM;
        AUTOMATED VERIFICATION SCRIPTS ARE EMPLOYED TO DETECT AND PREVENT
        UNAUTHORIZED ALTERATIONS.

        - This NOTICE format MUST NOT be modified, STRICTLY.

    - All repositories MUST STRICTLY contain the following METADATA documents:

        - AUTHOR
        - CHANGELOG

            - This MUST contain the changelog of this repository.
            - Each entry SHOULD respect the 83 characters column width.
            - Each entry SHOULD respect the conventional commits
              1.0.0 specification as described in this document:

                https://www.conventionalcommits.org/en/v1.0.0/

              with few caveats:

                - This document MUST only contain the following action types:

                    - fix
                    - feat
                    - build
                    - chore
                    - ci
                    - docs
                    - style
                    - test
                    - rfctr
                    - rvrt
                    - perf

                - rfctr SHOULD be interpreted as refactor.
                - rvrt SHOULD be interpreted as revert
                - All action types SHOULD have maximum character length of 5.

            - Each changelog item MUST be in this format:

                <YYYY-MM-DD> <action-type>: <concise-description>

                Example:

                    2025-12-20 chore: update documentation

            - Concise description MUST STRICTLY have a maximum character
              length of 65.
            - The format for each changelog item MUST STRICTLY consist of,

                - 10 characters date in YYYY-MM-DD format, followed by space then,
                - action type right padded to length 5, then colon and space then,
                - lastly, a maximum of 65 character length concise description.

        - CONTRIBUTING
        - CONTRIBUTORS
        - EMAIL
        - FLOW
        - FORMAT

            - This file itself.

        - INDEX

            - The target entry of this repository.

        - LICENSE

            - This MUST contain the license of this repository.
            - This MUST STRICTLY follow the FORMAT file.
            - This MUST only contain two sections, METADATA and License.

        - METADATA
        - ORIGIN
        - PRIVACY
        - README
        - REFERENCES
        - SECURITY
        - WEBSITE
        - VERSION

            - This MUST contain the version of this repository in SEMVER format.
            - SEMVER format MUST adhere to the format defined in,

                https://semver.org/

              with few caveats:

                - This MUST be in the RELEASE.MAJOR.MINOR format.
                - PATCH version MUST be interpreted as MINOR version.
                - CRITICAL changes MUST be interpreted as MAJOR version.
                - RELEASE version MUST start at zero.
                - A RELEASE version of zero MUST NOT be considered stable.
                - A RELEASE version of zero MUST NOT be used in production.
                - 99 MINOR versions MUST increment the MAJOR version.
                - 99 MAJOR versions MUST increment the RELEASE version.

            - Only the author MUST have the capability to update the VERSION file.
            - Version numbers MUST NOT reach 3 digits.


    - All single-line text formatted METADATA documents MUST be a single line
      with no line feed end of line and no final line feed.

    - All list text formatted METADATA documents MUST be multiple lines
      with line feed end of line and no final line feed.

    - All CONCISE-RFC-000000 documents MUST STRICTLY follow this structure
      in this order:

        X.  METADATA:

            This MUST contain the metadata of this document.

            The metadata of this document MUST STRICTLY follow this format
            in this order:

            - RFC:      CONCISE-RFC-000000
            - GROUP:    <GROUP-PROJECT-NAME>
            - TITLE:    <UNIQUE-CONCISE-DOCUMENT-TITLE>
            - ACRONYM:  <UNIQUE-CONCISE-DOCUMENT-ACRONYM>
            - AUTHOR:   <FIRST-NAME> <LAST-NAME> <email>
            - CATEGORY: (SPECIFICATION | INFORMATIONAL | EXPERIMENTAL)
            - STATUS:   (DRAFT | REVIEW | STABLE | DEPRECATED | OBSOLETE)
            - VERSION:  XXXXXX <X.X.X>
            - CREATED:  <YYYY-MM-DD>
            - CHECKSUM: <SHA-256>

        X.  Summary:

            This MUST contain the abstract of this document.

        X.  License:

            - This MUST contain the license text of this document.
            - This MUST only be used on LICENSE documents.
            - LICENSE documents MUST only contain this and the METADATA section.

        X.  Permission:

            - This MUST define the permissions for using, modifying, copying,
              and distributing this document and/or this repository.
            - This MUST contain the NOTICE for permission in this format:

                NOTICE: PERMISSION TO USE, MODIFY, COPY, AND/OR DISTRIBUTE
                THIS DOCUMENT AND/OR REPOSITORY IS GRANTED UNDER THE TERMS OF
                THE LICENSE AGREEMENT SPECIFIED IN THE LICENSE FILE.
                PLEASE REFER TO THE LICENSE FILE FOR DETAILS.

            - This MUST be contained in all CONCISE-RFC-000000 documents except
              the LICENSE file.

        X.  Contents:

            This MUST contain the table of contents of this document.

        X.  Document Status:

            This MUST contain the descriptive status of this document.

        X.  Normative Language:

            This MUST contain the normative language of this document.

        X.  Naming Conventions:

            This MUST contain the naming conventions of this document.

        X.  Structure:

            This MUST contain the structure of the repository and/or this document.

        X.  Compliance:

            This MUST contain the compliance of this document to this format,
            styles, principles, and tools which include any AI agent tools.

    - All CONCISE-RFC-000000 documents MUST follow these principles:

        - Single Responsibility Principle. CONCISE-RFC-000000 documents
          MUST address one and only one concern or feature.
        - Open-Closed Principle. CONCISE-RFC-000000 documents MUST be open for
          extension but closed for modification. Once the status is STABLE, the
          CONCISE-RFC-000000 documents MUST NOT be modified. New
          CONCISE-RFC-000000 documents MUST be created for updates. If an
          CONCISE-RFC-000000 document has issues, then the entire
          CONCISE-RFC-000000 document MUST be marked for deprecation and a new
          CONCISE-RFC-000000 document MUST be published.
        - Liskov Principle.
        - Interface Segregation Principle.
        - Dependency Inversion Principle.

    - All CONCISE-RFC-000000 documents MUST follow this style:

        - Section headers MUST be clear, concise, and well-defined.
        - Section headers MUST STRICTLY always define one and only one meaning.
        - Section contents MUST only contain the following styles,
            - Descriptive paragraphs in normal conversational English language.
            - Descriptive paragraphs must not contain complex
              conversational English words.
            - Lists that start with 1 hyphen (-) character followed by
              a single space and then the list item.
            - Formatted structures that are different from this format.
        - All formatted structures with ordered components MUST be STRICTLY
          followed.

    - All repositories MUST STRICTLY contain the following basic directories,

        - .vscode/
        - .github/
        - .husky/
        - dist/
        - public/
        - scripts/
        - src/
        - template/
        - tests/
        - todo/

            - All todo files MUST STRICTLY follow CONCISE-RFC-000000.
            - All todo files MUST STRICTLY end with *.todo file extension.
            - All todo files MUST STRICTLY be interpreted as text files.
            - There are five issue categories for todo,

                - critical
                - major
                - minor
                - prototype
                - reported

            - All todo files MUST STRICTLY follow the file name format:

                <priority>-issue-<YYYY-MM-DD>-<short-title>.todo

                Example:

                    critical-issue-2025-12-21-fix-e2e-tests.todo

8.  Compliance:

        - All AI agents MUST STRICTLY read the FORMAT file.
        - All AI agents MUST STRICTLY add to their context list this FORMAT file.
        - All AI agents MUST STRICTLY follow this FORMAT file.
        - All AI agents, STRICTLY, MUST NOT edit this FORMAT file.
        - All AI agents, STRICTLY, MUST NOT modify the VERSION file.
        - All AI agents MUST STRICTLY follow all rules containing the word
          STRICTLY.

|<------------------------------->[ ENDED-CRFCF ]<------------------------------->|
